  "prompt": "How should I start losing weight? I study in a hostel have no history of exercise whatsoever. I am 6'2 and 95kg approx.",
  "response": "Starting a weight loss journey while living in a hostel and having no prior experience with exercise can be challenging but definitely achievable with a structured approach. Here\u2019s a plan to help you get started:\n\n### Nutrition:\n1. **Assess Your Diet**: Start by reviewing your current eating habits. Identify areas where you may be consuming excess calories, such as sugary drinks, snacks, or large portion sizes.\n\n2. **Balanced Meals**: Aim for balanced meals that include protein, healthy fats, and whole grains. This helps in keeping you full longer and provides necessary nutrients.\n\n3. **Portion Control**: Pay attention to portion sizes, especially if you\u2019re eating in a canteen or mess where portions might be larger.\n\n4. **Increase Fruits and Vegetables**: Incorporate more fruits and vegetables into your meals. These are low in calories and high in nutrients.\n\n5. **Stay Hydrated**: Drink plenty of water throughout the day. Sometimes thirst is confused with hunger.\n\n6. **Limit Processed Foods**: Reduce consumption of highly processed foods, which tend to be higher in added sugars, unhealthy fats, and calories.\n\n### Physical Activity:\n1. **Start Slow**: Begin with activities you can manage and enjoy, such as walking or cycling. Aim for at least 30 minutes a day.\n\n2. **Bodyweight Exercises**: You can do exercises like push-ups, squats, and planks in your room. These don\u2019t require equipment and help build strength.\n\n3. **Find a Routine**: Explore fitness apps or online videos that offer guided workouts you can follow. \n\n4. **Be Active in Daily Life**: Take the stairs instead of the elevator, walk to nearby places, or try standing while studying.\n\n5. **Join a Group**: If possible, join a sports club or team. This can make exercise more enjoyable and help you stay motivated.\n\n### Lifestyle:\n1. **Set Realistic Goals**: Define clear, achievable goals. Aim to lose around 0.5 to 1 kg per week, which is a sustainable pace.\n\n2. **Track Progress**: Keep track of your weight loss, exercise, and food intake to stay accountable.\n\n3. **Get Enough Sleep**: Aim for 7-9 hours of sleep per night. Lack of sleep can affect hormones that regulate hunger.\n\n4. **Manage Stress**: Find stress-reduction techniques that work for you, such as meditation, reading, or listening to music.\n\n5. **Consistent Routine**: Consistency is key. Try to stick to your routine even during weekends or holidays.\n\n### Seek Support:\n1. **Buddy System**: Pair up with a friend who also wants to be active. You can encourage and motivate each other.\n\n2. **Professional Help**: If possible, consult with a nutritionist or a fitness trainer who can provide personalized advice based on your needs.\n\nStay patient with yourself, and remember that gradual changes lead to lasting results. The most important thing is to make sustainable changes that fit your lifestyle.",
